oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Workers with threshing equipment
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of several workers posing on and in front of threshing equipment. ""Frick Co. Waynesboro"" can be seen on the piece of equipment on left. ""A.B.F. Cox"" is written on and at the bottom of the photo. Note: this image appears on two separate negatives.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Agricultural equipment; Men; Horses
